<HEADLINE>
<P>
PENN STATE'S PRESIDENT THOMAS TO RETIRE IN 1995 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pennsylvania State University President Joab L. Thomas said Friday that he 
will retire next year. 
</P>
<P>
 Thomas, 61, said he probably would return to his native Alabama to work on at 
least two books. His contract expires Aug. 31, 1995. 
</P>
<P>
 Thomas came to Penn State in 1990 from the biology faculty at the University 
of Alabama. He previously was president at Alabama and chancellor at North 
Carolina State University. 
</P>
</TEXT>
