<P>
ADM. CROWE OKD AS ENVOY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Retired Adm. William J. Crowe, former chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff, 
has won Senate approval to be ambassador to Britain. Approval came Thursday on 
a voice vote with no opposition expressed on the floor. 
</P>
