<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: TUSTIN; SALVATION ARMY OPENS NEW CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Orange County chapter of the Salvation Army will mark the opening of its 
church and community center in Tustin Ranch with a concert today and a worship 
service on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The 45-piece Salvation Army band will perform at 7 p.m. at the new facility, 
at 10200 Pioneer Road.Tickets are $5 each. 
</P>
<P>
 The first service at the church will begin at 11 a.m. Sunday. At 3 p.m., Paul 
A. Rader, commander of the Salvation Army's USA western territory, will conduct 
the dedication ceremony for the church, community center and administrative 
offices in the complex. 
</P>
<P>
 "The Salvation Army is known for its extensive social service programs," said 
Capt. Lee R. Lescano, pastor of the new church and the Salvation Army's county 
coordinator, but it is "first and foremost a Christian church." 
</P>
<P>
 At a luncheon Friday, the Salvation Army honored several groups and 
individuals who performed volunteer services. 
</P>
