METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: VENICE; 2 TEEN-AGERS 
WOUNDED IN SHOOTING AT BUS STOP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A drive-by shooting in the Venice area has left two teen-agers wounded. 
</P>
<P>
 A 14-year-old girl and a 15-year-old boy were at a bus stop near Lincoln and 
Venice boulevards about 8:15 p.m. Thursday when they became involved in a 
quarrel with three men in a van, said Sgt. Dennis Barbello of the Los Angeles 
Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Shots were fired from the van, wounding the teen-agers, Barbello said. The 
girl was in critical but stable condition and the boy in satisfactory condition 
at UCLA Medical Center on Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Police were questioning a 24-year-old man in connection with the incident. The 
other suspects remained at large, Barbello said. 
