ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAGUNA HILLS; 2 BENEFITS TO AID SHELTER PROGRAMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The first of two benefits for the Ecumenical Service Alliance, a countywide 
group that runs a transitional homeless shelter for women and children, will be 
held this weekend. 
</P>
<P>
 Actress Morgan Brittany will be the host of the eighth annual Afternoon Tea & 
Bubbly on Sunday from 2 to 4 p.m. at 10841 Hideaway in Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
 The group will also sponsor a tennis tournament at the UCI Tennis Center on 
May 21. 
</P>
<P>
 Proceeds from the events will aid Martha's House, a shelter for women and 
children, and other alliance programs. 
</P>
<P>
 The Laguna Hills-based organization provides shelter and emergency assistance 
to people suffering from spousal abandonment, eviction, foreclosure, major 
medical expenses, loss of job, fire and other emergency situations.  
</P>
<P>
 The cost of Sunday's tea is $25. Those attending will be serenaded by a string 
trio and are eligible for door prizes such as a hand-painted porcelain Morgan 
Brittany doll. 
</P>
<P>
 The event will also feature a showing of watercolor paintings by Carolyn 
Westfall.  
</P>
<P>
 Reservations can be made by calling (714) 544-7534. 
</P>
<P>
 There is no charge for attendance at the tennis charity event, which will 
feature demonstration matches by pros Gretchen Galt Miller and Dick Miller. 
Tournament matches for women, men and mixed doubles will be played throughout 
the day. 
</P>
<P>
 For information, call (714) 588-7422. FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
