<TEXT>
<P>
 Three landscape architects will share the job of caring for Thousand Oaks' 
namesake trees, working together to keep the city green. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura resident George Moore, who has served as Thousand Oaks' sole tree 
protector for nearly a decade, will now split his duties with two friends: 
local landscape architects John Innes and Richard Campbell. Each consultant 
will earn $50 an hour. 
</P>
