<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. SANITATION DISTRICT HIRES SAN CLEMENTE'S CITY CONTROLLER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEN HALL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 City Controller Michael White announced this week that he is leaving to take a 
similar job with the Orange County Sanitation District. 
</P>
<P>
 White, 39, a San Clemente resident who has worked for the city for more than 
five years, accepts a new controller position recently created at the Fountain 
Valley-based district. 
</P>
<P>
 In San Clemente, White headed an accounting department of about 20 people and 
a city with a $56-million annual budget. At the sanitation district, White will 
work in a finance department that is overseeing a $635-million annual budget. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a step up for me, but I'm looking forward to the challenge," White said. 
</P>
<P>
 His salary range will also increase from a maximum of $6,105 a month in San 
Clemente to $7,730 a month at the sanitation district. 
</P>
<P>
 White's last day with the city will be May 27. No decision has yet been made 
whether to promote a San Clemente staff member or to recruit a controller from 
the outside, White said. 
</P>
<P>
 In the interim, senior accountant Brad Cagle will take over as controller. LEN 
HALL 
</P>
</TEXT>
