<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOLF ROUNDUP; SHEEHAN MOVES INTO SHARE OF LEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Patty Sheehan blew past the competition with a three-under-par 68 to gain a 
share of the lead after two rounds of the windswept LPGA Championship Friday at 
Wilmington, Del. 
</P>
<P>
 Sheehan, the defending champion, started the day in a 10-way tie for 17th 
place at 72. She had four birdies and one irksome bogey for a two-under 140 
total, and was tied with Robin Walton. 
</P>
<P>
 Walton offset a double-bogey and a bogey with four birdies for a 70. Alice 
Ritzman shot a 73 for a 141. 
</P>
<P>
 Sheehan, Walton and Ritzman were the only players under par after two trips 
over the 6,386-yard DuPont Country Club course. For a second consecutive day, 
players had to contend with swirling winds up to 30 m.p.h. 
</P>
<P>
 "The wind gusted and came from everywhere," Ritzman said. "It seemed like it 
changed direction every five seconds. It was a nightmare." 
</P>
<P>
 The cut was at nine over, the highest on tour this year. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Butch Baird and Bobby Nichols, non-winners on the Senior PGA Tour since 1989, 
got off to good starts to possibly break the string at the PaineWebber 
Invitational at Charlotte, N.C. 
</P>
<P>
 Nichols, who has come close to winning at the TPC at Piper Glen the previous 
two years, shot a six-under-par 66. Baird was the first to reach the clubhouse 
with that total as he birdied his last three holes. 
</P>
<P>
 Tom Shaw and Dale Douglass were at 67. Arnold Palmer, who designed the course 
and is the designated host for the event, struggled to a 75. 
</P>
<P>
 Baird's last victory was in 1989 and he has only one top-10 finish in 29 
tournaments. Nichols is looking for his second victory on the Senior PGA Tour, 
which he and Baird both joined in 1986. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 For the second day in a row, overnight rains washed out play in the Byron 
Nelson Classic at Dallas. More rain is forecast for the weekend as tournament 
organizers try to get in three rounds of play. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story; Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA051494-0094 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 041518 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
May 14, 1994, Saturday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 3; Column 1; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
