<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHAVEZ VICTORY HAS READERS FIGHTING MAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For all of you who think Julio Cesar Chavez is a great fighter, I'll let you 
in on a little secret: He got whipped by Pernell Whitaker, and was twice 
soundly beaten by Frankie Randall. The only reason Chavez is still champion is 
because of Don King's money.He has bought Chavez the title. 
</P>
<P>
 NATE SULLIVAN 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Barbara 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Dr. Flip Homansky's lack of ring savvy wreaked havoc on boxing on May 7. It's 
bad enough championship fights don't go 15 rounds. Now Homansky's ruling in the 
Julio Cesar Chavez-Frankie Randall fight strikes a low blow at what little 
integrity boxing has left. 
</P>
<P>
 Ringside's Dr. Death stopped the fight in the eighth round with three seconds 
left. He stopped the fight because Chavez said he didn't want to continue. 
Incredible. Of course, Don King loved it. His hair sizzled. Another grudge 
match. Another payday. 
</P>
<P>
 JIM SKEESE 
</P>
<P>
 San Diego 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 There are no hard and fast rules for boxing anymore. They just make them up as 
they go along. 
</P>
<P>
 DICK MASTRO 
</P>
<P>
 Hollywood 
