<HEADLINE>
<P>
TANSLEY, GOODRICH WIN BIG WEST TRACK TITLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton's Mike Tansley and Traci Goodrich of UC Irvine won 
individual titles during the first day of the Big West Conference track and 
field championships Friday at Las Cruces, N.M. 
</P>
<P>
 Tansley won the 3,000-meter steeplechase in 9 minutes 21.30 seconds, four 
seconds faster than second-place Mike Davidson of Utah State, defending 
conference champion in the event. 
</P>
<P>
 Goodrich won the women's 10,000 in 37:52.17.Fullerton's Heather Killeen was 
third in 38:18.19. 
</P>
<P>
 In the men's 10,000, Irvine's Todd Coulston was second in 32:44.43 and Tony 
Castellon of Fullerton was third in 32:59.14. Fullerton's Casie Lozano was 
third in the women's long jump in 18 feet 3 1/4 inches. 
</P>
<P>
 The Fullerton men are tied for third with UC Santa Barbara with 17 points. 
Irvine is sixth with 13 points. Utah State is first with 71. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton's women are fourth with 12 points. Irvine is tied with New Mexico 
State with 10 points. Utah State is first with 40. The competition concludes 
today. 
</P>
