<P>
PREP SWIMMING / SOUTHERN SECTION FINALS; FRESHMAN HELPS BUENA WIN TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM DERMODY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Freshman Rebecca Gilman of Ventura Buena performed like a seasoned veteran 
Friday night in the Southern Section Division I swimming championships at Long 
Beach's Belmont Plaza Pool. 
</P>
<P>
 Gilman led the Buena girls to the team title with victories in the 200- and 
500-yard freestyle events, and also swam anchor on the Bulldogs' victorious 
200-yard medley relay squad. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Barbara's Lindsay Gassner also won two events, the 50 freestyle in 23.76 
seconds and the 100 freestyle in 50.74. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine Woodbridge swimmer Derya Buyukuncu broke his Southern Section record 
and set a new national standard in the 100-yard backstroke with a 47.50 
clocking. A member of the 1992 Turkish Olympic swimming team, Buyukuncu also 
won the 50-yard freestyle in a Southern Section record 20.27. 
</P>
<P>
 Mission Viejo's Bart Sikora finished first in the 100-yard butterfly and 
500-yard freestyle. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine's Jason Lezak, second to Buyukuncu in the 50 freestyle, touched ahead 
of defending champion Matt Cornue of Villa Park in the 100 freestyle. Earlier, 
Cornue won the 200 freestyle. TIM DERMODY 
</P>
</TEXT>
