<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIVISION III TRACK AND FIELD; LAGUNA HILLS' BOYKIN SAILS TO VICTORY IN 800 
METERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT FARMER, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tiffany Boykin highlighted the Orange County contingent at the Southern 
Section Division III track and field preliminaries Friday night at Long Beach 
College. 
</P>
<P>
 The Laguna Hills junior ran away from the field early, winning the 800 meters 
in 2 minutes 18.15 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the fastest time of the evening, edging Trabuco Hills standout Peggy 
Hall by over two seconds. Hall was the second-fastest qualifier (2:20.51) and 
also qualified for the 400 final (1:00.42). 
</P>
<P>
 "I wanted a fast time today, but I guess I ran a dumb race," said Boykin, who 
ran the opening 400 lap in a blistering 1:04.2. 
</P>
<P>
 "I slowed down too much in the third 200. I really couldn't judge how fast I 
was running," added Boykin, who has the county's second-fastest time in the 
event this season. 
</P>
<P>
 Her teammates Tayyiba Haneef (high jump) and Heather McGlone (3,200 meters) 
easily qualified for next Saturday's section finals. 
</P>
<P>
 Other County highlights included: 
</P>
<P>
 -- Trabuco Hills' girls' 400-meter relay squad qualified in a season-fastest 
49.79. Mustang sprinter Rosie Manning also qualified for the 200-meter final, 
in 26.0. Manning also qualified with a wind-aided season-best in the 100 meters 
(12.40). 
</P>
<P>
 -- Laguna Hills' hurdler Shaheed Qassim ran 15.0 in the 110 highs and 40.70 in 
the 300 intermediates, easily advancing in both. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Estancia junior Johann Appell easily qualified in the 3,200, posting a 
career-best of 9:31.24. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Laguna Hills' discus thrower Jesse MacDonald posted the second-best mark in 
the competition, qualifying for the divisional final with a 154-foot-2 effort. 
Century senior Ronny Aristando also qualified for next week's discus final. 
</P>
