</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Huntington Beach defeated visiting Marina, 6-4, Friday to earn the Sunset 
League's final automatic berth for the Southern Section Division I baseball 
playoffs, knocking out Marina in the process. 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach (18-9, 8-6 in league) finished third behind Servite and 
champion Fountain Valley.Marina ends the season 17-10, 7-7. 
</P>
<P>
 The Oilers took the lead with three runs in the third inning. Trailing, 5-0, 
in the sixth, Marina scored four runs but stranded the potential tying and 
go-ahead runs. Huntington Beach added a run in the bottom of the sixth, when 
pinch-runner Brett Fish scored from third on a delayed double steal. 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach received a strong performance from junior right-hander Ryan 
Evans (4-0), who was making his first start. Evans, who had not previously 
pitched more than two innings in one appearance, held Marina scoreless through 
five innings. Viking left-handed senior starter Jim Sipkovich (5-4) took the 
loss. 
</P>
<P>
 Evans was relieved with two outs in the sixth after giving up two runs. Senior 
left-hander Bryce Dillard, who started in left field, pitched a scoreless 
seventh to earn his second save. Dillard also drove in two runs with sacrifice 
flies. JASON H. REID 
