<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEA VIEW LEAGUE BASEBALL RACE NARROWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Sea View League race to determine the league's Nos. 2 and 3 
representatives for the Southern Section Division III baseball playoffs became 
a little less crowded Friday afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
 Tustin won the league title, but five teams finished tied for second.Athletic 
directors from those schools held a lottery Friday morning, drawing four 
numbers out of a hat. As a result, four teams played Friday afternoon and 
Irvine received a bye. 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar defeated Woodbridge, 2-1, and Saddleback beat Santa Margarita, 
7-4. Saddleback then won a coin toss with Corona del Mar to gain a playoff 
berth. Corona del Mar will play Irvine today at Tustin High School at 2 p.m., 
with the winner also qualifying for the playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 The Nos. 2 and 3 spots will be determined by regular-season head-to-head 
competition, with Corona del Mar getting the No. 2 berth if it wins Saturday 
and Saddleback the No. 2 berth if Irvine wins. A league's third-place team is 
almost guaranteed a first-round playoff game on the road. 
</P>
</TEXT>
