 In the Olympic League: 
</P>
<P>
 Calvary Chapel 4, Brethren Christian 2 -- Alex Oklend and Ryan Blood each had 
two hits for visiting Calvary Chapel (16-8, 8-4), which advances to the 
Division V playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Orange League: 
</P>
<P>
 Anaheim 7, Savanna 5 -- Damien Marquez had two doubles and two RBIs, and Jaime 
Carlos had two singles and two RBIs for host Anaheim (10-16, 5-10). Savanna 
(10-15, 7-8) still qualifies for the Division II playoffs as the league's No. 3 
team. 
</P>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda 14, Magnolia 2 -- Mike Brambilla had three hits and three RBIs and 
Jason Theis had two hits and four RBIs to lead Brea-Olinda (21-4, 11-4). 
Brambilla and Theis each hit home runs. 
</P>
<P>
 The Wildcats finish as co-champions with Valencia. 
</P>
