 In the Pacific Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
 Estancia 4, Laguna Beach 2 -- Estancia (13-12, 9-6) finishes tied for second 
with Century, but gets the league's No. 2 playoff berth. Jose Cabrera (8-3) 
pitched a five-hitter, striking out eight for the Eagles. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills 8, Century 5 -- Brett Nista had three hits and two RBIs for 
Laguna Hills (13-12, 8-7), which scored seven runs in the seventh. Nista scored 
one run to finish with 128 in his career, adding to his county record and 
placing him seventh on the Southern Section's all-time list. 
</P>
