<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; NEWPORT HARBOR GETS AROUND FOUNTAIN VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PETER BARZILAI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Newport Harbor Coach Dan Glenn breathed a sigh of relief Friday after his team 
beat visiting Fountain Valley in the first round of the Southern Section 
Division I boys' volleyball playoffs, 15-10, 15-5, 13-15, 15-9. 
</P>
<P>
 After losing to Corona del Mar in the Sea View League final -- the Sailors 
shared the league title with the Sea Kings -- Glenn said he was afraid his team 
might be primed for an upset. 
</P>
<P>
 "I was real nervous," Glenn said. "Fountain Valley is real young and real 
good, and plus losing that last match was real disappointing. But, the kids 
came back well tonight." 
</P>
<P>
 In the first three games, the Sailors (14-4) jumped out to early leads. 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor led, 12-3, in the first game, but Fountain Valley (12-5) scored 
six consecutive points before the Sailors put the game away. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sailors then won the second game with ease, but the Barons fought back in 
the third game after trailing, 10-6. 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley closed out its comeback by scoring the final six points. 
</P>
<P>
 "There were a lot of runs," Glenn said. "Both teams made a lot of mistakes 
though." 
</P>
<P>
 The Sailors put together their biggest run in the fourth game, when they 
scored 10 points, taking a 10-3 lead. Mitch McCoy had four aces during the 
streak. 
</P>
<P>
 McCoy finished with a match-high 15 kills and Eric Vallely had 11 for the 
Sailors. Ed Ratledge led Fountain Valley with 14 kills. PETER BARZILAI 
</P>
</TEXT>
