<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIVISION II DIVING; CORONA DEL MAR'S ZUBRIN, SONORA'S JENKINS WIN TITLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MELANIE NEFF 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sandy Zubrin of Corona del Mar calmly won her third consecutive Southern 
Section Championship Friday at Heritage Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Showing little emotion, except for a small grin, Zubrin, 17, scored 529.25, 
never scoring lower than a 6.On her sixth-round dive, a reverse pike, she drew 
three 9s and followed with an inward pike that earned four 8.5s. 
</P>
<P>
 Even with Zubrin's impressive performance, second-place Laura Segundo of 
Arcadia finished only 21 points behind. 
</P>
<P>
 "The scores were really close this year," said Zubrin, winner of the 1993 
Summer Nationals. "This year's competition was better than in the past." 
</P>
<P>
 Only 40 points separated third-place Erin McGinty (485.95), a junior from 
Santa Margarita, and teammate Caroline Kelley (445.40) in seventh. 
</P>
<P>
 Sonora's Aaron Jenkins won the boys' event with 464.45, 66 points ahead of 
second-place Peter Kransz of Sunny Hills. Jenkins led from the beginning, 
scoring 6.5-7.5 on his first dive, a forward pike. 
</P>
<P>
 Four Sonora boys finished among the top eight. Jason Jass (397.20) finished 
third, Larry Neberman (363.20) sixth and Jeff Stewart (355.75) eighth. Troy's 
Derek Mittenzwei was fourth (386.00). MELANIE NEFF 
</P>
</TEXT>
