<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFF THE TICKER: GOOFY BANK ROBBER STORY NO. 4,781 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Trying to disprove the adage that crime doesn't pay, a man who tried to rob a 
Charlotte bank has sued the bank for $15 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Amil Dinsio, 58, who, along with relatives, tried to hack a hole in the roof 
of United Carolina Bank two years ago, sued the bank in federal court here. 
</P>
<P>
 Dinsio claims his 46-month prison sentence is too long because the bank 
exaggerated the amount it could have lost ($272,000) had the robbery been 
successful -- which it was not. 
</P>
<P>
 Dinsio, now in a federal prison in Loretto, Pa., says the $15 million in his 
suit was "just a figure." 
</P>
<P>
 "It's what you do in lawsuits," he said. "I'd be happy with a couple of 
million." 
</P>
</TEXT>
