<TEXT>
<P>
 Firm Seeks to Compete With Pacific Bell, GTE: Teleport Communications Group 
asked the California Public Utilities Commission to allow it to compete against 
the companies in the local telephone market.The two big phone utilities hold 
monopolies on such service throughout most of California. Current law prohibits 
competition, but state regulators have indicated they intend to open 
telecommunications services to all comers, including cable companies. Teleport, 
based in Staten Island, N.Y., wants to offer local phone service to companies 
providing access to the Internet and other computer-based information 
resources. 
