BRIEFLY: LABOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Striking Workers Picket Zacky Headquarters: Employees from Zacky Farms' 
Commerce processing plant picketed the poultry company's El Monte headquarters 
to highlight their demands for safer working conditions and pay equality with 
other Zacky sites. About 120 members of the United Food and Commercial Workers 
Union Local 770 went on strike May 5 after nine months without a contract.The 
next day, Zacky told them they would be permanently replaced if they did not 
return to work by Monday. However, instead of replacing the strikers, Zacky 
staffed the plant with managers and temporary workers and opened negotiations 
with the UFCW through federal mediators. Unless it receives a satisfactory 
offer from Zacky, the UFCW said, it will expand the strike to the El Monte 
distribution center, which could interrupt chicken shipments to supermarkets. 
</P>
