<P>
'THE PAPER' IS RATED R 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In regard to Charles Neal's May 7 letter ("No, Not Everybody's Laughing at the 
Movies"): 
</P>
<P>
 So, Neal saw people leave the film "The Paper" with their children before it 
ended. Excellent idea.The movie is definitely, emphatically unsuited for 
children. 
</P>
<P>
 An R rating should alert filmgoers that there is something iffy about a film's 
message. They might then check it out in advance, so their afternoons can be 
more pleasant. 
</P>
<P>
 I am appalled by explicit sex and violence, so I read reviews and boycott 
films that contain it. I am not appalled by explicit language when it fits the 
context, which this did. I found the movie hilarious and Neal's distress more 
out of bounds than the film's vocabulary. 
</P>
<P>
