<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; MINORS TO HELP POLICE IN LIQUOR SALE STING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Oxnard police will be sending "baby-face" teen-agers into liquor stores 
throughout the city as part of a sting operation to end illegal sales of 
alcohol to minors, police announced Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Police will ask cadets and students, ages 17 or 18, to go into businesses and 
try to buy alcohol, said Detective Bob Camarillo, who is heading the sting 
operation. If a store clerk asks for identification, the decoys will present 
driver's licenses showing their real age, Camarillo said. 
</P>
<P>
 "We have to use baby-face minors," Camarillo said. The program will begin next 
week and continue through the second week of June. 
</P>
<P>
 Businesses found violating the law will face fines and could lose their 
alcohol licenses, Camarillo said. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
