two men who robbed the passengers of their jewelry and money. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said the hijackers, two "very well-dressed" black men in their 20s, 
boarded the bus with the Norwegians at Miami International Airport. 
</P>
<P>
 As the bus left the airport, one of the men pulled a gun and ordered the 
driver to head east on a nearby highway. The other man then robbed the 
tourists, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 One of the robbers punched a woman in the face, police Detective Marie 
Duboulay said. 
</P>
