<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Panorama and San Fernando community hospitals completed a merger Friday, 
changing the name on both facilities to Mission Community Hospitals. 
</P>
<P>
 The hospitals will operate under a two-campus structure, with the San Fernando 
facility, 700 Chatsworth Drive, specializing in psychiatric care, and the 
Panorama City facility, 14850 Roscoe Blvd., providing full primary health care. 
</P>
