</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Up With People, an international student performing group, is looking for 
families in the San Fernando Valley to house their cast of 150 during the 
group's tour later this month. 
</P>
<P>
 The group of students, ages 17 to 25, will be in the area May 22-29.They will 
perform at Pacoima and Haddon elementary schools in Pacoima, Oxnard Elementary 
School in North Hollywood and Lassen Elementary in North Hills, said 
spokeswoman Jennifer Hunnicutt. 
</P>
<P>
 Host families, which are asked to provide breakfasts and dinners for a week 
and transportation to shuttle points, will receive two complimentary tickets to 
performances, Hunnicutt said. 
</P>
<P>
 The group's World in Motion Tour consists of a two-hour musical show of 
international contemporary songs and dances performed for students in grades 
four through six, Hunnicutt said. 
</P>
<P>
 "We try to help develop a greater sense of understanding for other cultures in 
their communities," Hunnicutt said. 
</P>
<P>
 The students represent 22 countries and all speak English. Up With People is 
based in Broomfield, Colo. JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
