<P>
CAR COLLISION LEAVES 1 DEAD, 2 INJURED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHAU LAM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Glendale man was killed and two others were seriously injured when his car 
crashed into a car making a left turn into a driveway, authorities said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Eric Nikoian, 25, died Thursday at the scene of the 9:50 p.m. accident in the 
6700 block of Whitsett Avenue in North Hollywood, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Nikoian was a passenger in a car driven by 18-year-old Nazaret Abovian of 
North Hollywood, who remained at Northridge Hospital Medical Center, where he 
was being treated for head and facial injuries.  
</P>
<P>
 Another passenger, Lyla Bennett, 21, of Glendale, also remained hospitalized 
at North Hollywood Medical Center, where she was treated for a fractured right 
wrist and broken legs, said a hospital spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver of the car making the left turn, Guadalupe Jose Gutierrez, 26, of 
North Hollywood, was not hurt in the collision. He was not cited. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said that Gutierrez was driving northbound on Whitsett Avenue near 
Vanowen Street when he made a left turn into a driveway. A southbound car 
rammed into Gutierrez's car and crashed into two parked vehicles. CHAU LAM 
</P>
