<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; $500,000 IN JEWELRY STOLEN FROM SHOP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Four men robbed an Antelope Valley jewelry store Friday of diamond rings, 
bracelets and necklaces worth $500,000, Los Angeles County sheriff's deputies 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
 The men, two of them armed with handguns, stole more than 800 items from 
Barry's Jewelers in the Target Plaza on West Avenue K about 11:30 a.m., said 
Deputy Will Roemermann of the Antelope Valley Sheriff's Station. 
</P>
<P>
 The jewelry was taken along with $200 in cash, he said. The men drove off in a 
white Jeep Cherokee with Arizona license plates, according to witnesses. 
</P>
<P>
 No employees were hurt in the robbery and no customers were in the store, 
Roemermann said. 
</P>
<P>
 A witness wrote down the car's license plate number and gave it to police, he 
said, but no suspects have been arrested. 
</P>
