</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF FLETCHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mike Scyphers, Simi Valley High's suspended baseball coach, filed a grievance 
Friday with the Simi Valley Unified School District, claiming he was suspended 
without proper notice, Scyphers' attorney Brian O'Neill said. 
</P>
<P>
 Scyphers, 41, was suspended May 3, pending police and district investigations 
into possible financial and disciplinary improprieties.The district has 
maintained that Scyphers' right to five days' notice does not apply because he 
was suspended from his job as coach, not as a teacher. 
</P>
<P>
 O'Neill said it is now up to the district to resolve the matter or it will go 
to arbitration. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a time-consuming process," O'Neill said. "It's unlikely this issue is 
going to be resolved during this school year." 
</P>
<P>
 The Pioneers completed the regular season Friday with a 7-2 victory over 
Channel Islands. JEFF FLETCHER 
